  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (faults-physical gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The pump is deployed in continuous in vivo clinical use with documented exposure to bearing wear, motor voltage fluctuations, and sensor drift over multi-hour bypass runs. Fault tolerance considerations are documented elsewhere. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
